-- Siemens Chairman Considering Resignation, Sueddeutsche Reports
-- B y   J a m e s   K r a u s
-- 2012-07-24T23:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-24/siemens-chairman-considering-resignation-sueddeutsche-reports.html
Siemens Supervisory Board Chairman
Gerhard Cromme is considering resigning his position,
Sueddeutsche Zeitung reported, citing unidentified members of
the board in a preview of an article to appear today.  The board is discussing several possibilities, the
newspaper said. Cromme may take over as head of the Krupp
Foundation, replacing Berthold Beitz, SZ added.  To contact the reporter on this story:
James Kraus in London at 
 jkraus2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
